President Barack Obama has sent a letter to the Speaker of the House and the President of the Senate, stating that the national emergency with respect to the Democratic Republic of the Congo will continue beyond October 27, 2016. The situation in the country, which has been marked by widespread violence and atrocities, poses a threat to regional stability and the foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, President Obama has determined it is necessary to continue the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13413.